    "During the 2015-2018 subperiod, the \"K-degree\" keyword transitioned to module 15 out of 39 modules, with a slightly higher PageRank score of 0.00478.",
    "This indicates growing attention to K-degree approaches, likely due to their simplicity and computational efficiency for anonymizing social networks.",
    "In the 2019-2022 subperiod, the keyword moved to module 7 out of 32 modules, reflecting a higher-ranked position, but with a reduced PageRank score of 0.00310.",
